The United States Senate is being urged to take action to protect the constitutional right to vote, which is currently facing attacks from proponents of the "Big Lie" and Republican officials across the country. Senate Democrats are pushing for the start of a debate on the Freedom to Vote Act, a bill that includes bipartisan provisions. However, Senate Republicans are expected to block even the debate on the bill, as they have done in the past with other voting rights bills. The article argues that it is crucial to protect democracy, as it is the essence of America. The right to vote freely, fairly, and have votes counted is considered fundamental and should be simple and straightforward. The author calls for a debate and a vote on the matter.